Live from the Sun Arena, Time Square, Pretoria JOHANNESBURG - Zozibini Tunzi has been crowned Miss South Africa 2019. The Eastern Cape beauty takes over the crown from last year's winner Tamaryn Green. Tunzi beat 15 other dazzling young women from across the country to scoop the prestigious crown. IN PICTURES: Miss SA top 16 finalists The 25-year-old walks away with a lucrative R3-million prize package, which includes a R1-million cash prize, a new car and a fully-furnished apartment for the year of her reign. The Miss SA pageant celebrated its 61st anniversary on Women's Day. The event took place at Time Square in Pretoria. Zozibini Tunzi is a 25-year-old completing her BTech in PR from Cape Town.  Her role models are her parents and Caster Semenya, whom sheâ€™d love to meet. Zozibini is a hard-core Marvel fan, was a Game of Thrones addict and enjoys eating out.  Who is your favourite Marvel superhero? #ZoziForMissSA #DreamWalker #MissSA2019 A post shared by  Miss South Africa (@official_misssa) on Jul 11, 2019 at 3:24am PDT